50|$|In general, a live {{television}} program was more common for broadcasting content produced specifically for commercial {{television in the}} early years of the medium, before technologies such as <b>video</b> <b>tape</b> appeared. As <b>video</b> <b>tape</b> <b>recorders</b> (VTR) became more prevalent, many entertainment programs were recorded and edited before broadcasting rather than being shown live.|$|R
