50|$|Magnetic tape is {{a medium}} for {{magnetic}} recording, made of a thin, magnetizable coating on a long, narrow strip of plastic film. It was developed in Germany, based on magnetic wire recording. Devices that record and play back audio and <b>video</b> using magnetic <b>tape</b> are <b>tape</b> <b>recorders</b> and <b>video</b> <b>tape</b> <b>recorders.</b> A device that stores computer data on magnetic tape is a tape drive (tape unit, streamer).|$|R
