50|$|A {{hard disk}} {{recorder}} (HDR) {{is a system}} that uses a high-capacity hard disk to record digital audio or digital video. Hard disk recording systems represent an alternative to reel-to-reel audio <b>tape</b> recording and <b>video</b> <b>tape</b> <b>recorders,</b> and provide editing capabilities unavailable to <b>tape</b> <b>recorders.</b> The systems, which can be standalone or computer-based, typically include provisions for digital mixing and processing of the audio signal.|$|R
